emuInput.TitMainTitle: Street corner with three or four story apartment building in housing project, and boy on tricycle, McKees Rocks, another version
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1955, pg. 5, reads: "Another Hershman Battle - Another battle with McKees Rocks Burgess David Hershman, the so-called 'boss,' centers on his redevelopment plans which will wipe out three churches, and the Trinity AME Zion's lot, above picture, which is oblique to the Housing Project (lower picture) which the church says contains many of its members and makes the lot a logical spot for a new church. - Harris Photo."
